# Originality Statement

## What existed before
Most teams implement quality checks inconsistently (ad-hoc scripts, dashboard checks, or one-off Great Expectations suites) and treat governance as separate from reliability.

## What is unique here
This framework unifies:
- quality SLIs/SLOs,
- policy-as-code governance,
- scoring + trend reporting,
- audit/evidence packaging,
in one repeatable structure that can be applied to multiple domains.

## Why it matters
It converts “data trust” from opinions into measurable metrics and standardized controls, enabling leadership visibility and compliance readiness.


